{"key":"post-5478385","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5478385</id>\n<content>Do not use vaseline or soap on the lids, or you'll grow nothing but green.  First, get your petri dishes out of the incubator.  Petri dishes should be grown out at room temperature.  Second, store the dishes in a vertical stack.  The condensation is caused by the temperature difference between the inside and outside of the petri dish.  Stacking dishes vertically equalizes the temperatures and prevents condensation.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-27/070264929-rhizomorphic_myceliumaa.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/05-27/070264929-thumb_rhizomorphic_myceliumaa.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5478541</next>\n<prev>5477313</prev>\n<first>5476557</first>\n<last>5478541</last>\n<when>1144162480</when>\n<utime>04/04/06 05:54 PM</utime>\n</post>"}